{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb4440 
Parties typically settle cases rather than proceeding to a trial and judgment. However, obtaining a favorable settlement is a complex process involving many factors. This Note discusses some of the factors that influence whether, when, and how to settle litigation pending in California state court. Specifically, it details the factors counsel should consider when contemplating and advising clients on the benefits and disadvantages of settling a dispute. It also offers ways to successfully present and correctly time a settlement offer.
