{\b1 \cf21 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs28 \li0 
{\b1 \cf21 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs28 \sa0 \sb0 
Settlement Timing
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
If the client intends to settle, it is generally better to finalize the terms quickly before the client incurs additional legal costs and the parties\rquote  positions become too entrenched. While the prospect of settlement should be evaluated throughout the life of a dispute, there are several factors to consider about a settlement\rquote s timing.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \i0 \fs18 
