\par 
}
{\b1 \cf21 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs24 \li0 
{\b1 \cf21 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs24 \sa0 \sb0 
Before Proceedings Begin
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
Both sides may benefit from settling the dispute as soon as it arises, mostly because of the costs they save by avoiding discovery and attorney\rquote s fees. An early settlement is particularly appropriate where maintaining the relationship between commercial parties is a priority, in which case counsel should pursue settlement before the situation becomes irreversibly adversarial (see 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_anchor_a000012_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf20 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
Commercial Considerations
}}}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
). However, even parties that do not have a lengthy or ongoing relationship may benefit from the cost savings associated with early negotiations, since greater amounts spent litigating the dispute may diminish the funds available to settle a lawsuit or pay any resulting judgment.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
To begin settlement talks at this stage of a dispute, counsel should:
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 {\fi-360 \li {\*\pn \pnlvlblt \ilvl0 \ls44 \pnindent0 \pnf1 {\f2 \pntxtb \u8226\'3f}}{\listtext \b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li480 \u8226\'3f\tab }\ls44 {\pntext }
{\pard }\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li480 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li480 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs18 \li480 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa180 \sb160 
Address the parties\rquote  long-standing business relationship (if one exists) and the client\rquote s interest in continuing it.
\par {\pntext }
}
}
}
}{\fi-360 \li {\*\pn \pnlvlblt \ilvl0 \ls45 \pnindent0 \pnf1 {\f2 \pntxtb \u8226\'3f}}{\listtext \b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li480 \u8226\'3f\tab }\ls45 {\pntext }
{\pard }\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li480 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li480 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \ql \fs18 \li480 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa180 \sb160 
Stress the ongoing alignment of the two parties\rquote  business interests and how settlement can preserve the benefits of that relationship by working together.
\par {\pntext }
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri90 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li90 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs18 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb180 
In certain circumstances, plaintiff\rquote s counsel may wish to consider drafting (but not filing) a complaint and providing it to the proposed defendant. This can help to define the legal and factual issues and can also show the defendant that the plaintiff is serious about pursuing the matter.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f0 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
